2.text: Study these. Here’s your cap. - The cap is yours. He took my book last week. - The book is mine. You forgot to take your cap . - It’s yours. He went to see his paddy field. - The paddy field was his.

3.text: We use possessive pronouns to refer to ownership. Possessive pronouns replace nouns in sentences.
